Summary: Dutchie Pay - Get updated user account balances
Release Notes:
This release updates how we gather bank account balances for customer transactions.

Previously, we were not getting a fresh balance with each transaction. 

This update gets a fresh balance check when the customer completes their Ecomm order. If an additional order (or pickup of the original order) occurs within 2hrs, the balance is not updated (due to a current limitation on the MX side). If the pick-up or additional order occurs >2hrs, a fresh balance will be provided from MX.

Summary: Dutchie Pay | Improved Payment Error Codes
Release Notes:
Updates to error messaging that results from customers attempting to complete purchases using Dutchie Pay on Ecomm.

Error codes is included with each message. This error code can be used as a reference by both the customer and for support.

Support can develop scripts around each error code to provide the customer with additional details.

Define, Document & Implement Naming Conventions for  Staging Phase
Release Notes:
This story creates a naming convention for new locations during the onboarding process for customers. New customer locations will automatically default to staging (isLive = False) now rather than to production as the current process provides. A new naming convention for these staging locations is required so everyone can clearly identify a location in this phase. 

* If a location isLive = False, the tag “Staging” is appended to end of location name at creation
* When a location is published (isLive = True), the tag is removed from the location name

Summary: Auto-create New Locations as "Staging" Locations
Release Notes:
This story creates a new process. During the onboarding process,  new customer locations will automatically default to staging (isLive = False) rather than to production as the current process provides. 

* If a location isLive = False, the tag “Staging” is appended to end of location name to identify it as staging. 
* Implementation specialists will work with customers to import, configure and test in the new staging location. 
* New staging tools will be created for the Implementation Specialists to allow them to wipe data from the location and, when ready, publish the location to production (isLive = True).

Release Notes:
Adds a new page under superuser to host new super user management capabilities:

* This new page will act like Settings → Users except that it shows all super users in the system
*  When a users permission is edited, it allows only the selection of the super user level permissions

Summary: Create Location for IS to Publish to Production
Release Notes:
This feature creates a new sub-menu item  in the in LLx Left-side navigation bar for Superusers -

* Super Users > Publish

A new Publish page provides a feature for Implementation Specialists that allows them to publish a staging location (isLive = False) to live (isLive = True). 

* Publish is a one-time event 
* Publish is permission-based for select Implementation Specialists
* Publish is no longer available once the location is published and goes live

Summary: Create New Permissions for Data Wipe
Release Notes:
Adds new permission for Super User’s with Edit permissions. If they enable the permission it grants Implementation Specialist superusers access LLx>Superusers>Staging Tools>Data Wipe:  

* Super User permission for the Data Wipe feature requires the Implementation Ops team (who have Super User Edit permissions) to grant access 
* The Data Wipe page is blocked by a Super User Edit permission - it is visible only to those with access

Summary: Create New Permissions for Publish to Production
Release Notes:
Adds a permission for Superusers with Edit permissions. The feature provides the ability to enable select implementation specialists access to the new Publish page, available while a location is in Staging. 

* Publish is permission-based for select Implementation Specialists
* Permission enables access to new sub-menu item  in the in LLx Left-side navigation bar - Superusers > Publish
* Superuser with Edit permissions (such as Implementation Ops) grant access 
* Publish is no longer available once a location is published and goes live (isLive = True)
* The Publish page is blocked by a Super User Edit permission - it is visible only to those with access

Summary: Update Superuser Menu
Release Notes:
Adds a new Staging Tools section to the LLx Superuser menu: 

* Visibile to superusers
* Available to superusers only during the staging phase of the customer onboarding

Under this new Staging Tools section, adds the following menu items:

* Data Import
* Data Wipe
* Publish

Summary: Create Permissions for State Pack/Config Mods, Add Account and Add Location
Release Notes:
Adds new permission for Super User’s with Edit permissions. If they enable the permission it grants Implementation Specialist superusers access to the following:  

* Account Creation (these Superusers are able to create new LSP)
* Location Creation (these Superusers are able to create new locations for LSPs)
* State Pack Modifications (these Superusers can create and modify state templates)
